Tytus entered North Freeport in a daze. He was greeted by Sir Breel who was just a squire when Tytus left. &quot;Could it be? Sir Tytus Steele? By Marr it is so good to see you after so long!!&quot; Tytus drew his sword and with one a masterful slash beheaded Breel where he stood. The assualt began. He layed waste to any paladin that stood in his way to the Hall of Truth. At the hall he had the full powers of Veeshan guiding him he took out most of the guard. Sentries came running from the Temple to assist in the defense. Tytus's body was battered. It was only the power of Veeshan that kept him going. She was not finished yet. Tytus made it to the top level of the Hall and stood face to face with Valeron Dushire. Valeron called off the assault. Tears welling up in Valeron's eyes he looked upon the shell that used to be the boy he raised. &quot;What sort of evil has done this to you son?&quot; Son. The word pierced through the powers that Veeshan held over Tytus. She had lost him again. In her last fit of rage she struck him down. Valeron rushed to Tytus's broken body laying on the stone floor. Tytus looked up and Valeron with emotion pouring out of him as he lay dying. &quot;You called me son. I failed my birth father, and I have failed the only father I have ever really known. Can you forgive me?&quot; Valeron looked past all the blood and the wounds on the face and only saw that boy he had raised as his own. &quot;Of course you are forgiven. You could have given in to the evil power but you fought it even though it meant your life. You lived your life with honor my son. Now your real father awaits you in the plane of valor.&quot; Tytus closed his eyes, and with his last breath he managed to smile.  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/utytus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tytus</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0> at: 5/6/01 6:22:49 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowra